    "details": {
      "cr": 8,
      "type": {
        "value": "undead"
      },
      "alignment": "neutral evil",
      "biography": {
        "value": "\n                        Once a brilliant but morally bankrupt scholar named Alaric Thorne, he delved too deep into forbidden lore, seeking immortality and ultimate arcane mastery. His pursuit led him to pacts with dark entities and dangerous rituals that ultimately consumed his mortal form, transforming him into a lich-like undead. He now exists as 'The Whispering Sage,' a hollow shell driven by an insatiable hunger for knowledge and the dark influence of his patron.\n                        <hr>\n                        <p><strong>Behavior:</strong> The Whispering Sage is a cold, calculating entity that seeks to amass forbidden knowledge and power. It views mortals as tools or obstacles, to be manipulated or eliminated as needed. It prefers to operate from the shadows, using its vast magical prowess to achieve its goals indirectly, but will engage directly if necessary, unleashing devastating spells with chilling precision.</p>\n                        <p><strong>Appearance:</strong> The Whispering Sage appears as a gaunt, desiccated humanoid figure draped in tattered, dark robes that seem to absorb light. Its skin is parchment-like and stretched taut over bone, with empty sockets where eyes once were, now glowing with faint, malevolent purple energy. Wisps of shadowy mist constantly emanate from its form, carrying faint, unsettling whispers.</p>\n                        <p><strong>Twist:</strong> The Whispering Sage is not merely a spellcaster but a vessel for a fragment of a forgotten, malevolent deity of secrets and decay. Its true goal is to gather enough arcane power to fully manifest its divine patron into the material plane.</p>\n                        <p><strong>Habitat:</strong> Unknown</p>\n                        <p><strong>Treasure:</strong> The Whispering Sage hoards ancient tomes, magical components, and artifacts of power. Its lair is likely filled with valuable scrolls, rare spell components, and potentially cursed relics.</p>\n                    "
      },
